latestPosts.caption:
உருவம் பொலிந்த
ஊனின் அகத்துள்
நெருப்பின் செறிவே 

Stylist and concept : @styledby._.p 
📸: @theyashwantmohan 
Muse : @the.bindi.bitch 

So this is about feminine energy.
At her core, the feminine is said to be soft receptive, nurturing, calm.
Until 
A boundary is crossed, a wound touched.
And that softness? It rises.
It becomes rage ! not petty anger, but sacred, feminine rage.
Powerful. Loud. Demanding the respect 

It can feel overwhelming.
But she’s not alone.
Other women other feminine energies hold her.
They don’t silence her. 
They witness her.

And in that safe space, she breathes.
She remembers who she is.

The rage softens.
She returns to her wholeness.

Not just soft. Not just wild.
But the full Goddess.
 
Written @_bykanmani 

Direction and art 
a team effort ❤️🌺

latestPosts.caption:
Mint Street ‘25 
by Neeraj Make & Kanmani 

One of the oldest streets in Chennai, believed to be the longest. 
Named during the 1840s when the British East India Company set up its coin-making facility. 
An accidental colour collage, created by the painted doors of every home.
A study of history through surface, texture, tone, photography, and fashion.
-nm
